  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When user did not agree to use camera and clicked \"Do not show again\" on the camera permission popup, the next time he tries to scan QR code following screen is shown: \r\n\r\nWhen trying to scan contact QR code:\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/42273886-df5577fa-7f8a-11e8-9739-21aa7c1063f1.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\nWhen trying to scan wallet QR address:\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/42273909-fb8961ca-7f8a-11e8-98df-3edd9eb558ab.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\nUser can easily leave the screens by pressing back button. When permissions are granted in system settings, all works fine. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nError popup on Android should appear saying: \"To grant the required camera permissions, please go to your system settings and make sure that camera permissions are enabled for Status app.\" Similar popup appears on iOS. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nNo error popup.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Wallet and scan QR code of an address\r\n- Deny camera permissions and select \"Do not show again\" the permissions popup\r\n- Scan the QR code again\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, July 4\r\n* Operating System: Android\r\n",
